16/10/2006
BRCKO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The new International Supervisor of Brcko District, Raffi Gregorian, cited the strengthening of Brcko's external policy and representation in state institutions as priorities, during a news conference Friday (October 13th). 
Gregorian, who assumed the post on October 1st, said he would seek to resolve issues related to allocation of revenues from VAT collection and to enhance judicial integration between district and state authorities. 
He also spoke about updating Brcko's legislation and its harmonisation with the state-level laws as another priority. 
(Nezavisne novine - 14/10/06; OHR Sources, PBS BiH - 13/10/06)
